The evidence with the title 'Americans think we have the World's Best Colleges. We don't ... ' says Jun 28, 2014  ... When mr. Obama said , “ in eighth-grade math, we've fallen to ninth place, ” he was referring to the average score of eighth graders . He didn't say anything about how many of the world 's 13-year-old math geniuses were American. International university rankings , moreover, have little to do with education. 
